  "commentary": "With SPX at 6756.65 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma at the 6755 strike (-7093M), dealers are forced to sell into weakness and buy rallies, creating amplified volatility around current levels. The recent GEX surge (-61.6% in 1min, -76.9% in 5min) suggests we just hit a pocket of heavy dealer hedging activity, likely triggered by movement through these key negative gamma strikes between 6745-6765. Watch for continued chop between the 6745 support (where negative gamma lessens) and resistance at 6800 where positive gamma kicks in - dealers will be buying any dip toward 6745 but selling aggressively if we push toward 6800.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile ping-pong action between 6745-6800 with dealers amplifying moves in both directions.",
